tryll s list: August edition — tryll What is tryll tryll s list Sign Up What is tryll tryll s list Sign Up August , tryll official tryll s list: August edition tryll official August , tryll s list: August edition tryll official August , This is the story of Archibald, Archibald the Many many years ago, our beloved tryllbird, embarked on a mission: discover experiences across the world, to personally recommend to his And so it was that Archibald, armed with positivity, enthusiasm and determination set out from Egypt, flying miles and miles until arriving at his first stop: New York Since his arrival, Archibald has been exploring the Big Apple, He has been dropping feathers in spots that he has most enjoyed and is now, finally, excited to share them with us Hotels citizenM “ The only hotel I’ve ever found that gives me a gallery, gorgeous NYC view and great coffee all at ” — Archibald As NYC hotels go, citizenM Bowery is a triumph in comfort and coolness The huge open plan lobby serves as a coffee shop, space and casual bar all rolled into Once you’ve perused the stacks of coffee table books and walls full of artwork in the lobby you’ll find that the best is yet to come, as you ascend through citizenM’s The entire staircase is home to The Museum of Street Art, with every floor bringing you to a new design piece, and finally to Cloud Nine (literally) - citizenM’s chic rooftop bar, where summer drinks come with a side of gorgeous Manhattan The Nomad Hotel Decorated with classic antiques that give it a comforting and timeless feel, the Nomad Hotel is an attention The building was previously home to the National Cash Register Company, but has since been fully restored to remind guests of a grand European hotel while still providing a unique New York The Nomad also has a Michelin Star, making it worthy of a stop even without a Food DeKalb Market Hall “ Less is More, but when it comes to food: I’ll take one of everything! ” — Archibald Ever craved the world famous Katz’s Deli pastrami sandwich, but not wanted to make the trip to the LES to get one? Dekalb Market Hall has got you This brand new underground food market in Downtown Brooklyn not only has a ‘Taste of Katz Deli’, but a taste of almost every cuisine you could ever Grab yourself whatever you’re craving, wash it down with a speciality wine from Brooklyn Wine Cellar, and check out the Ample Hills stand for Then, hang around into the night to catch a round of trivia or see your favorite comedian perform at Dekalb’s Stage Events! La Mercerie “ A little Paris in New York, how ” — Archibald Looking for an French restaurant in the city? La Mercerie opened two years ago when Chef Rose moved to New She started cooking with her grandparents in Paris in the French countryside and is on a mission to bring the sustenance of her childhood into this The menu changes once a day at Landmarks Flatiron “ Well, definitely not that stingy for a piece of pie ” — Archibald Without a question, the Flatiron Building is one of the most emblematic and icons of New York However, not too long ago and rather surprisingly, this was not the Our beloved triangular building was depicted as a “monstrosity”, a “stingy piece of pie” and “unfit to be in the Center of the City”. Well, we surely admire our stingy piece of pie, and would argue that regardless of how many times you’ve walked past it, it’s hard not to pause and contemplate its majesty and elegance even just for a few West Street Courts Also known as “The Cage”, the West Courts is notorious for its intense basketball games on its sized Several NBA players began their love of the sport on these courts, among them being J, Walter Berry, and Jayson “The Cage” attracts more than ,000 spectators each summer, with many of them attending its citywide annual Take the ACE to West , and watch some of the most talented players in the world rough out a game of pure Drinks Special Club “ This Special Club is jolly special and rather ” — Archibald An ode to New York lounges where you could eat and drink while jazz, soul or blues bands would be playing in the background, the Special Club will make you feel as though you’ve been let in on a little, special Phones Spend the next two hours feeling connected to the people you’re sharing this magical experience with, be it your friends or your table City Vineyard & Wine Garden If you’re looking for a place to capture that memorable sunset photo with your friends, City Vineyard & Wine Garden is Pair a glass of your favorite vino with some oysters and soak up the sun as you lounge on its roof This restaurant and wine bar sits on the Hudson River in Tribeca, and has a panoramic view of downtown Manhattan and the Shopping Showfields “The Most Interesting Store in the World” goes to Showfields, an only Armed with a slide and pillow pit, explore each room and immerse yourself in the story of each Showfields brings online brands to life through interactive retail and invites customers to touch, smell, and te
